# RevPay – Digital Wallet & Business Payments Platform

## Project Documentation

---

# 1. Introduction

RevPay is a full-stack financial web application designed to provide secure digital payment services for both personal and business users. The platform enables 
users to manage digital wallets, perform peer-to-peer transactions, track financial activities, and receive real-time notifications through a web-based interface.

The system supports two types of users: **Personal Account Users and Business Account Users**. 
Personal users can send and receive money, manage payment methods, monitor transaction history, and maintain their digital wallet. 
Business users receive additional capabilities such as accepting payments, generating invoices, managing customers, applying for loans, and analyzing business performance through analytics dashboards.

RevPay is developed using modern enterprise technologies such as **Spring Boot for backend services, Spring Security for authentication and authorization, 
Thymeleaf for server-side rendering, and Oracle Database for data management**. The application follows a **modular and layered architecture** consisting of 
controllers, services, repositories, and models.
The platform emphasizes **security, scalability, and usability**, implementing role-based access control, transaction validation, and secure password encryption. 
By integrating financial operations with modern web technologies, RevPay demonstrates the implementation of a secure and scalable digital wallet and business 
payment management system.

