# 2. Objectives of the Project

The primary objectives of the RevPay project are:

• To develop a secure digital wallet platform for financial transactions
• To enable peer-to-peer money transfers between users
• To allow users to manage payment methods and wallet balance
• To provide business users with tools for payment collection and invoice management
• To implement role-based authentication and authorization
• To provide transaction tracking and financial analytics
• To demonstrate full-stack web application development using enterprise frameworks

---

# 3. Scope of the Project

The scope of RevPay includes developing a web-based platform that supports digital financial transactions and business payment management.

Personal users can:

• Register and log in securely
• Send and receive money
• Request payments from other users
• Manage payment methods such as debit or credit cards
• View transaction history
• Add money to wallet
• Withdraw money from wallet
• Receive notifications for financial activities

Business users can:

• Accept payments from customers
• Generate invoices and manage billing
• Track business revenue and financial analytics
• Apply for business loans
• View loan repayment schedules
• Monitor payment trends and customer activity

The system is designed for **educational and demonstration purposes**, but its architecture allows it to be extended into a scalable financial platform.

