# 5. System Architecture (Three-Tier Architecture)

RevPay follows a **three-tier architecture**, separating the system into independent layers for better scalability, maintainability, and security.

The three layers include:

1. Presentation Layer
2. Application Layer
3. Database Layer

---

## 5.1 Presentation Layer (User Interface)

The Presentation Layer provides the user interface where users interact with the system.

Functions include:

• Login and registration forms
• Wallet dashboard
• Transaction pages
• Payment request interfaces
• Invoice management screens
• Business analytics dashboard
• Notification center

Technologies used:

• HTML
• CSS
• JavaScript
• Bootstrap
• Thymeleaf

This layer sends user requests to the application layer and displays the response returned by the system.

---

## 5.2 Application Layer (Business Logic)

The Application Layer processes system logic and handles all operations related to transactions, security, and financial workflows.

Main responsibilities include:

• User authentication and authorization
• Transaction processing
• Wallet balance management
• Invoice generation and payment processing
• Loan application processing
• Notification handling

Technologies used:

• Spring Boot
• Spring Security
• Hibernate

---

## 5.3 Database Layer (Data Storage)

The Database Layer stores all persistent system data.

Data stored includes:

• User accounts
• Business profiles
• Wallet balances
• Transactions
• Payment methods
• Loan applications
• Invoices
• Notifications

The database used is:

• Oracle Database

