# 8. Functional Modules

The RevPay system is divided into several functional modules.

---

## 8.1 Authentication and Security Module

This module manages user identity verification and secure system access.

Features include:

• User registration
• Secure login authentication
• Password encryption
• Role-based access control
• Transaction PIN management

Spring Security is used to protect system resources.

---

## 8.2 Wallet and Transaction Management Module

This module manages financial transactions within the platform.

Features include:

• Send money to other users
• Request money from users
• Accept or decline payment requests
• Add money to wallet
• Withdraw funds
• View transaction history

---

## 8.3 Payment Method Management Module

Users can manage their linked payment methods.

Features include:

• Add credit or debit cards
• Edit card details
• Delete payment methods
• Set default payment method

---

## 8.4 Invoice Management Module (Business)

Business users can generate and manage invoices.

Features include:

• Create invoices with item details
• Add customer information
• Set payment terms and due dates
• Track invoice status
• Mark invoices as paid

---

## 8.5 Loan Management Module (Business)

This module allows business users to apply for loans.

Features include:

• Submit loan application
• Upload supporting documents
• Track loan approval status
• View loan details
• Make loan repayments

---

## 8.6 Analytics Dashboard Module

Business users can monitor financial performance.

Features include:

• Revenue reports
• Transaction summaries
• Payment trends
• Outstanding invoices
• Top customers analysis

---

## 8.7 Notification System

The system provides real-time notifications for important activities.

Notifications include:

• Money received
• Payment requests
• Transaction confirmations
• Invoice updates
• Loan application status

